body: "## Context\nFiled by the 2026-07-03 concurrency audit: `pm claim <id>` performed a silent takeover when the item was already assigned to another agent — two parallel agents could both believe they own the same item, breaking multi-agent work distribution. Only a warning (`claim_takeover`) was emitted, which agents don't reliably read.\n\n## Design (implemented, uncommitted as of 2026-07-04)\n- Claim is now an atomic test-and-set: if the item is held by a different author and neither `--force` nor `--if-available` is passed, claim throws a CONFLICT PmCliError with code `already_claimed_by`, naming the current holder.\n- Error carries agent-actionable guidance: why (parallel agents must never proceed believing they co-own an item) and nextSteps — `pm next` to pick different work, `--if-available` for a no-op skip, `--force` only for coordinated takeover.\n- `heldByOther` now treats empty/whitespace-only assignee as unheld (previously an empty-string assignee counted as \"held\", blocking claims on effectively unassigned items).\n- Semantics matrix: unheld → claim succeeds; held + `--if-available` → skip with `claim_skipped_held_by` warning (exit 0); held + `--force` → takeover with `claim_takeover:prev->new` warning; held + neither → CONFLICT `already_claimed_by`.\n- tests/unit/commands/claim-command.spec.ts updated for the new conflict contract.\n\n## Constraints / decisions\n- `--force` keeps the takeover path (needed for reclaiming from dead agents); the fix removes only the SILENT steal default.\n- Terminal-item claim still requires `--force` (pre-existing rule, unchanged).\n- The claim mutation itself runs under the item lock, so with pm-2muu's lock wait this is a true test-and-set (read assignee + write happen atomically w.r.t. other mutators)."
